AgentBOM — Dual Licensing Notice

This repository contains components under different licenses:

┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Component                  │ License                             │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Discovery Engine           │ PolyForm Internal Use 1.0.0         │
│ (CLI, scanners, detectors) │ See LICENSE_ENGINE                  │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ Agent BOM Schema           │ MIT License                         │
│ (/schema directory)        │ See LICENSE_SCHEMA                  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Why This Split?

1. Discovery Engine (PolyForm Internal Use):
   - The CLI and detection logic are available for internal business use
   - You may use, modify, and run it within your organization
   - You may NOT provide it as a service to third parties or commercialize it
   - Prevents vendors from repackaging and selling the scanner

2. Schema (MIT):
   - The Agent BOM JSON Schema is fully open and permissive
   - Maximizes adoption and interoperability
   - Anyone can implement, extend, or build tooling around it

Quick Reference:

- Using the CLI internally? ✓ Allowed (PolyForm Internal Use)
- Modifying detectors for your org? ✓ Allowed (PolyForm Internal Use)
- Adopting the schema in your own tools? ✓ Allowed (MIT)
- Selling AgentBOM as a SaaS? ✗ Not allowed (PolyForm restriction)
- Building commercial tooling that reads/writes Agent BOM files? ✓ Allowed (schema is MIT)

For Questions:

If you're unsure whether your use case is permitted, please open an issue
or contact the maintainers.

